📖 Step-by-Step Breakdown
🔷 STEP 1 — Application Analysis
File: applicationAnalysisGuidelines.txt Supplement: CNDApplicationGuidlines.txt(optional).txt

Purpose: Train the AI to deeply understand the CND application before any testing begins.

What the AI Does:

Phase	Action
Phase 1	Discovers project structure — tech stack, directories, build tools
Phase 2	Maps user journeys and screen-by-screen navigation flows
Phase 3	Identifies features — CRUD, Search, Data Viz, Reporting
Phase 4	Catalogs UI components, API integrations, state management
Phase 5	Assesses test readiness and prioritizes areas for coverage
CND-Specific Knowledge Added (from optional file):

Navigation pattern: Login → Dashboard → Search (CLLI) → Category Tab → Module → Subcategory
Engineering Category modules: Floor Plan, Equipment Search, Connection Detail, Cable
Key UI components: SearchBarNew.js, .search-engine__input, modal dialogs, zoom controls
Floor Plan specifics: Graphic/Tree View, Zoom In/Out/Reset, Rack interactions, Change Floor Plan modal
Output: A comprehensive understanding of the app that the AI carries into Step 2.

🔷 STEP 2 — Test Case Generation
File: testGenerationGuidelines.txt

Purpose: Generate structured, human-readable test cases in JSON format based on the app knowledge from Step 1.

Test Case Format (Option 2 — Recommended):

{
  "case_description": "Verify Floor Plan module loads via Engineering category",
  "test_steps": [
    {
      "step_number": "TS_01",
      "action": "Open Browser and navigate to CND Application URL",
      "expected_result": "The SSO Login Page is displayed successfully"
    },
    {
      "step_number": "TS_02",
      "action": "Enter valid username and password",
      "expected_result": "Credentials are entered successfully"
    }
  ],
  "modules_impacted": ["FloorPlan.js", "SearchBarNew.js"],
  "test_complexity": "5"
}
Coverage Rules: | Category | Distribution | |----------|-------------| | Functional Test Cases | 80% — Business logic, CRUD, workflows | | UI Navigation Test Cases | 20% — Menus, routing, deep-linking | | Performance / Security | ❌ Out of Scope |

Complexity Rules: | Level | Range | Description | |-------|-------|-------------| | Low | 1–4 | Single module, 5–7 steps, simple CRUD | | Medium | 5–7 | 2-module interaction, 7–20 steps | | High | 8–10 | ❌ NOT ALLOWED |

Navigation Flow Standard (all CND tests follow this):

Step 1:  Launch Browser → Enter CND URL
Step 2:  SSO Login (username + password)
Step 3:  Dashboard loads
Step 4:  Click Search bar → Enter CLLI/criteria
Step 5:  Select Engineering/Template category tab
Step 6:  Select module (e.g., Floor Plan)
Step 7:  Select subcategory (e.g., Site Code/CLLI)
Step 8:  Execute module-specific test steps
🔷 STEP 3 — Automation Code Generation
File: CucumberTestGenerator.txt

Purpose: Convert the JSON test cases from Step 2 into executable Java/Cucumber/Serenity test code — integrated with the existing CND-DomainFramework.

What Gets Generated:

CND-DomainFramework/
  src/test/
    resources/features/
      └── [Module]Tests.feature        ← Gherkin scenarios
    java/starter/
      stepdefinitions/
        └── [Module]StepDefinitions.java  ← @Given @When @Then
      teststeps/
        └── [Module]Actions.java          ← Screenplay Task classes
      pageobjects/
        └── [Module]Page.java             ← UI element locators (if new)
Golden Rules for Code Generation:

Rule	Detail
🚫 Never modify existing files	Only extend — never break existing tests
♻️ Reuse first	Login, navigation, search steps already exist — reuse them
✅ Real UI interactions	Use Click.on(), Enter.theValue(), WaitUntil.the(), Ensure.that()
🔍 Module-specific step names	@When("the {actor} clicks the Floor Plan {string} button")
⏱️ Wait conditions mandatory	Every UI interaction must have WaitUntil before it
✅ Verification at every end	Every scenario must close with a Then verifies... step
Verification After Generation:

# 1. Compile check
mvn clean test-compile

# 2. Full test run + Serenity report
mvn clean verify
